You don't want this number.

300
00:23:01.505 --> 00:23:03.552
I'm gonna get a new number tomorrow.

301
00:23:03.632 --> 00:23:05.221
- You're getting a new number?
- There he is.

302
00:23:05.301 --> 00:23:07.264
Rhi. That's not Steve's cousin.
I don't even think he's gay.

303
00:23:07.344 --> 00:23:08.846
- What?
- I'm sorry. I have to go.

304
00:23:08.929 --> 00:23:10.142
- I'll explain later. Promise.
- What?

305
00:23:10.222 --> 00:23:11.394
Where are you going?

306
00:23:12.182 --> 00:23:13.354
Go. go. go.

307
00:23:15.686 --> 00:23:16.904
Hell. no.

308
00:23:17.521 --> 00:23:19.524
- Wait. you guys.
- Come on. come on.

309
00:23:19.648 --> 00:23:20.945
Leave him alone.

310
00:23:22.192 --> 00:23:23.444
Don't creep on our women. little dude.

311
00:23:23.527 --> 00:23:24.528
Rhi. give me my keys.

312
00:23:24.612 --> 00:23:26.660
No. Justin. you can't.

313
00:23:26.822 --> 00:23:28.324
- Justin.
- My keys.

314
00:23:28.407 --> 00:23:30.410
No. you cannot drive right now.

315
00:23:30.492 --> 00:23:31.869
Who even was that?

316
00:23:53.057 --> 00:23:55.230
Siri. Hey. Siri.

317
00:23:56.518 --> 00:23:57.736
Do I have a phone?

318
00:23:58.187 --> 00:24:00.736
<i>It is 6:29 a.m.</i>

319
00:24:17.331 --> 00:24:19.709
<i>This teenager missed curfew.</i>

320
00:24:19.792 --> 00:24:21.920
<i>then said the Devil made him do it.</i>

321
00:24:22.086 --> 00:24:24.633
<i>Monroeville's Nathan Daldry was found asleep</i>

322
00:24:24.713 --> 00:24:26.427
<i>around 1:00. Saturday morning</i>

323
00:24:26.507 --> 00:24:29.471
<i>by the side of a highway</i>
<i>with a broken back windshield.</i>

324
00:24:29.551 --> 00:24:30.973
<i>His explanation?</i>

325
00:24:31.053 --> 00:24:32.305
<i>He had been possessed by Satan...</i>

326
00:24:32.388 --> 00:24:33.856
Your boy took down his social media.

327
00:24:34.264 --> 00:24:36.103
- <i>So. tell us what happened.</i>
- Guess I gotta talk to him in person.

328
00:24:36.183 --> 00:24:37.981
Justin. what are you thinking?

329
00:24:38.227 --> 00:24:39.729
Leave him alone. He's disturbed.

330
00:24:39.812 --> 00:24:41.485
Then why were you even hanging out with him?

331
00:24:43.107 --> 00:24:44.108
I don't know.

332
00:24:47.111 --> 00:24:49.783
So. Friday night he was super weird.

333
00:24:49.863 --> 00:24:52.491
And then. this morning.
I get a text from a random number.

334
00:24:53.867 --> 00:24:56.586
"If you meet me in person.
somewhere public. I can explain.

335
00:24:57.204 --> 00:24:58.422
"Please come alone."

336
00:24:58.747 --> 00:25:00.169
Oh. my God. Are you going to?

337
00:25:00.332 --> 00:25:01.675
I don't know. should I?

338
00:25:02.292 --> 00:25:03.419
I think you have to.

339
00:25:03.502 --> 00:25:05.596
This is the coolest. creepiest thing
that has ever happened.

340
00:25:35.034 --> 00:25:36.707
Tell me you're alone. You're alone. right?

341
00:25:37.995 --> 00:25:39.872
I'm sorry. do I know you?

342
00:25:39.955 --> 00:25:41.548
Nathan sent me.

343
00:25:43.834 --> 00:25:46.838
Oh. um... Where is Nathan?

344
00:25:47.588 --> 00:25:48.760
He's here.

345
00:25:49.173 --> 00:25:51.301
In a way. I mean. he's not. like. here. here.

346
00:25:51.383 --> 00:25:52.972
but he also wasn't there on Friday
when you met him.

347
00:25:53.052 --> 00:25:54.395
Or you thought that you met him.

348
00:25:55.596 --> 00:25:56.768
You know. you actually didn't.

349
00:25:57.097 --> 00:25:58.315
What?

350
00:25:59.058 --> 00:26:00.401
Today. I'm Megan.

351
00:26:00.976 --> 00:26:04.105
The day that you met Nathan.
I was Nathan. All right?

352
00:26:04.188 --> 00:26:06.610
And the day that Amy shadowed you
at school. I was Amy.

353
00:26:06.690 --> 00:26:08.909
And the day that
you went to the beach with Justin...

354
00:26:10.527 --> 00:26:11.779
I was Justin.

355
00:26:12.946 --> 00:26:17.327
Because I am someone who wakes up
in a different body every day.

356
00:26:19.745 --> 00:26:23.124
Always someone my age.
Never too far from the last.

357
00:26:23.207 --> 00:26:24.880
never the same person twice...

358
00:26:26.001 --> 00:26:28.755
I have absolutely no control over any of it.

359
00:26:29.546 --> 00:26:33.551
Okay. did Rebecca tell you I'd be here?
She wasn't supposed to tell anyone.

360
00:26:33.634 --> 00:26:35.432
I don't know why it happens.
I don't know how.

361
00:26:35.928 --> 00:26:38.306
I mean. this is...
No one's ever tried to explain it to me.

362
00:26:38.388 --> 00:26:41.392
And this is the first time
I've ever actually told anyone about it.

363
00:26:43.644 --> 00:26:45.772
And I know I'm not doing a good job.

364
00:26:49.775 --> 00:26:51.368
Okay. Well...

365
00:26:52.778 --> 00:26:56.373
Thank you. This is all very good.

366
00:26:57.366 --> 00:26:58.959
But I think I should go.

367
00:27:01.995 --> 00:27:03.497
"You have a nice smile."

368
00:27:03.789 --> 00:27:05.336
That was the fortune that you got.

369
00:27:06.125 --> 00:27:07.672
The fortune that we both got.

370
00:27:08.377 --> 00:27:10.299
You told me about the day
that your dad got laid off.

371
00:27:10.379 --> 00:27:11.550
You told me about the French restaurant.

372
00:27:11.630 --> 00:27:12.882
Okay. just stop.

373
00:27:12.965 --> 00:27:15.429
I told Justin those things. not you.

374
00:27:15.509 --> 00:27:17.181
He has nothing to do with this.

375
00:27:17.261 --> 00:27:20.060
He's the only one who does.
I spent the day with him.

376
00:27:20.722 --> 00:27:24.188
And now he and you and Nathan.
and God knows who else

377
00:27:24.268 --> 00:27:25.520
are playing some stupid joke.

378
00:27:25.602 --> 00:27:28.105
And. honestly. I don't even want to know why.

379
00:27:28.188 --> 00:27:31.112
- So just. please. stop.
- He doesn't talk to you like this.

380
00:27:32.568 --> 00:27:35.538
He doesn't spend days with you
like the one that we had together. okay?

381
00:27:36.822 --> 00:27:38.324
He doesn't see you.

382
00:27:43.036 --> 00:27:46.381
You have to know that that wasn't him.

383
00:27:48.709 --> 00:27:49.710
It's...

384
00:27:50.085 --> 00:27:51.678
It's not possible.

385
00:27:52.379 --> 00:27:53.597
It is.

386
00:28:08.854 --> 00:28:09.855
Hey.

387
00:28:10.314 --> 00:28:14.410
Hey. I'm all right.
I seem not all right to you? I'm fine.

388
00:28:15.110 --> 00:28:16.157
Great.

389
00:28:16.695 --> 00:28:18.914
Do you wanna study at my place after school?

390
00:28:19.990 --> 00:28:21.788
- "Study."
- Who's Megan?

391
00:28:22.743 --> 00:28:23.790
I don't know any Megan.

392
00:28:24.536 --> 00:28:27.915
Did you tell anyone about what I told you

393
00:28:27.998 --> 00:28:29.591
about what happened with my dad?

394
00:28:30.375 --> 00:28:31.376
Um...

395
00:28:31.752 --> 00:28:35.473
Honestly. I don't even remember
what you told me about your dad.

396
00:28:45.432 --> 00:28:48.527
What's wrong with you?
Are we hanging out or what?

397
00:28:52.856 --> 00:28:54.199
Whatever.

398
00:29:22.094 --> 00:29:23.767
Hey. It's me. A.

399
00:29:24.554 --> 00:29:26.773
Oh. Hi. um...

400
00:29:29.601 --> 00:29:30.602
Wait. "A"?

401
00:29:30.686 --> 00:29:32.563
He's James. but I'm A.

402
00:29:33.063 --> 00:29:35.862
Like. just A. like the letter.

403
00:29:36.858 --> 00:29:38.986
I'm still not convinced that this is real.

404
00:29:41.738 --> 00:29:43.411
Who named you A?

405
00:29:43.865 --> 00:29:47.540
I did. I wanted a name that no one else
was likely to have. so...

406
00:29:48.829 --> 00:29:50.877
Okay. the day you were Justin.
what was I wearing?

407
00:29:51.999 --> 00:29:53.842
Peasant blouse. jean shorts.

408
00:29:55.502 --> 00:29:56.503
What?

409
00:29:56.586 --> 00:29:58.133
You know what a peasant blouse is?

410
00:29:58.213 --> 00:30:00.385
Well. half the time I wake up as a girl.

411
00:30:00.465 --> 00:30:04.641
Although. I will say. I think that James
could totally pull it off. I think...

412
00:30:04.803 --> 00:30:06.646
Got the physique for it. all that good stuff.

413
00:30:06.805 --> 00:30:08.023
Okay.

414
00:30:10.100 --> 00:30:11.727
What was the last thing
I said to you that day?

415
00:30:12.769 --> 00:30:14.772
"Your mouth tastes so much better
when you don't smoke."

416
00:30:14.855 --> 00:30:16.443
And the name you called Justin to his face

417
00:30:16.523 --> 00:30:17.736
when you were Nathan?

418
00:30:17.816 --> 00:30:19.659
What? Oh. uh. Galahad.

419
00:30:20.777 --> 00:30:23.200
And when you were Amy.
who showed you around after I did?

420
00:30:23.280 --> 00:30:24.327
Alexander.

421
00:30:27.409 --> 00:30:31.333
You still could be a liar.
Just a ridiculously well-prepared liar.

422
00:30:31.413 --> 00:30:33.001
Or I could be telling you the truth.

423
00:30:33.081 --> 00:30:34.628
Or I could be going insane.

424
00:30:35.208 --> 00:30:37.798
I mean. who are you? Who are your parents?

425
00:30:37.878 --> 00:30:39.175
Do they switch bodies every day?

426
00:30:40.922 --> 00:30:43.095
Hey. do you mind if we go somewhere
a little more private?

427
00:30:43.175 --> 00:30:46.429
Okay. maybe if you were
a petite cheerleader again.

428
00:30:46.511 --> 00:30:49.810
But I'm not sure you fully realize this.
You're a big. threatening dude today.

429
00:30:49.890 --> 00:30:51.436
so. absolutely not.

430
00:30:51.516 --> 00:30:53.564
Right. I get it.

431
00:30:55.896 --> 00:30:57.273
I don't know if I have parents.

432
00:30:57.773 --> 00:31:02.370
Um. I assume so. but I have no one to ask.

433
00:31:03.278 --> 00:31:06.118
So. every day of your life.
you've just woken up. and...

434
00:31:06.198 --> 00:31:08.826
Just tried to live that day for that person.

435
00:31:09.493 --> 00:31:13.418
Not mess anything up for them.
make no mark. leave no trace.

436
00:31:14.289 --> 00:31:15.836
And you're never that person again?

437
00:31:16.249 --> 00:31:20.675
No. I might see them at school
a week or a month later.

438
00:31:21.254 --> 00:31:23.473
If I'm in the same area.

439
00:31:25.425 --> 00:31:30.682
So. like. when you're somebody.
are you them or still you?

440
00:31:30.764 --> 00:31:32.016
I'm me.

441
00:31:32.099 --> 00:31:34.443
You know. my consciousness. my memories.

442
00:31:35.394 --> 00:31:38.898
But then I can also access
their history and their memories.

443
00:31:39.356 --> 00:31:40.778
But not all at once.

444
00:31:41.316 --> 00:31:45.116
The longer I'm in someone that day.
the more I know about them.

445
00:31:48.657 --> 00:31:49.909
Who else have you told this?

446
00:31:49.991 --> 00:31:52.460
I told you. no one else.

447
00:31:52.953 --> 00:31:54.751
That sounds really lonely.

448
00:31:57.666 --> 00:31:58.667
Can be.

449
00:31:59.501 --> 00:32:00.628
And sad.

450
00:32:02.546 --> 00:32:04.093
But it isn't.

451
00:32:04.506 --> 00:32:08.181
Because I've seen so much.

452
00:32:09.928 --> 00:32:12.101
I know what makes each person different.

453
00:32:13.140 --> 00:32:15.017
And what makes everyone the same. you know?

454
00:32:15.100 --> 00:32:17.728
I've seen the same color blue

455
00:32:17.811 --> 00:32:21.156
look 50 different ways
with 50 different pairs of eyes.

456
00:32:23.191 --> 00:32:26.115
But you never get to stay with anything
long enough to watch it grow.

457
00:32:28.447 --> 00:32:29.619
It's true.

458
00:32:31.324 --> 00:32:33.702
But I'd like to. though.

459
00:32:38.623 --> 00:32:41.843
If I show you something.
will you promise to show no one else?

460
00:32:45.172 --> 00:32:46.219
Check out my Instagram.

461
00:32:53.138 --> 00:32:56.017
I've posted pictures any days that I could.

462
00:32:56.516 --> 00:32:59.395
Of people I've been.
and the things that I've seen.

463
00:33:00.145 --> 00:33:01.237
Of course. it's a risk.

464
00:33:01.563 --> 00:33:04.658
I have to scrub the login information
every night before I go to bed

465
00:33:05.901 --> 00:33:07.619
but it's good to have a record.

466
00:33:15.160 --> 00:33:17.584
This still doesn't prove anything.

467
00:33:18.663 --> 00:33:22.884
I mean. you could just be getting these
from other people or the Internet.

468
00:33:23.418 --> 00:33:25.466
I could. but I'm not. Wait. wait. wait.

469
00:33:26.796 --> 00:33:28.799
Can we please meet again?

470
00:33:30.425 --> 00:33:33.053
I don't know. Yes. maybe.

471
00:33:35.138 --> 00:33:37.937
Just let me process this
for a little while. okay?

472
00:33:38.725 --> 00:33:39.897
Okay.

473
00:33:40.060 --> 00:33:41.357
Bye. A.

474
00:33:42.729 --> 00:33:43.947
Bye.

475
00:34:31.486 --> 00:34:32.908
Did you need me?

476
00:34:35.490 --> 00:34:36.742
No.

477
00:34:37.284 --> 00:34:38.411
I'm good.

478
00:35:05.103 --> 00:35:06.321
Hey.

479
00:35:08.481 --> 00:35:09.528
It's me.

480
00:35:10.609 --> 00:35:11.701
Remember?

481
00:35:11.860 --> 00:35:14.074
Yet another person
has the unique idea to prank me

482
00:35:14.154 --> 00:35:15.867
by pretending to be the Devil.

483
00:35:15.947 --> 00:35:16.994
What?

484
00:35:19.159 --> 00:35:20.877
No. no. I. um...

485
00:35:22.287 --> 00:35:24.711
I'm hoping to write something
for my school newspaper.

486
00:35:28.376 --> 00:35:29.753
Actually. I do recognize you.

487
00:35:30.754 --> 00:35:31.881
You do?

488
00:35:33.548 --> 00:35:35.300
I'll meet with anyone
interested in the truth.

489
00:35:36.051 --> 00:35:37.303
Okay.

490
00:35:37.802 --> 00:35:39.391
See. he did something to my memory

491
00:35:39.471 --> 00:35:41.849
so the whole night's kind of hazy.

492
00:35:42.599 --> 00:35:43.691
But...

493
00:35:46.061 --> 00:35:47.734
I remember dancing.

494
00:35:48.980 --> 00:35:49.981
Then...

495
00:35:50.774 --> 00:35:52.947
I was in this unnaturally tiny house.

496
00:35:54.444 --> 00:35:56.913
Then running for my life.

497
00:35:57.697 --> 00:36:01.292
Apparently. that evening. I told my mom
that he needed to borrow a car

498
00:36:01.409 --> 00:36:03.833
so I could go help some friends
write a musical about Jesus.

499
00:36:04.746 --> 00:36:06.339
And this should go in your story.

500
00:36:07.415 --> 00:36:08.962
When he was within me.

501
00:36:09.042 --> 00:36:11.340
he used my phone
to access his Instagram account.

502
00:36:13.755 --> 00:36:15.928
I was on Satan's social media.

503
00:36:16.883 --> 00:36:19.762
It was intense.

504
00:36:21.346 --> 00:36:24.521
It was a record of all the other
teenagers that he's taken over.

505
00:36:25.767 --> 00:36:26.985
Can I see?

506
00:36:27.310 --> 00:36:29.357
He kicked me off and changed the password

507
00:36:29.437 --> 00:36:31.401
before I could save any of the photos

508
00:36:31.481 --> 00:36:33.529
but I recognize you.

509
00:36:34.442 --> 00:36:36.695
- What do you mean?
- From one of the photos.

510
00:36:37.404 --> 00:36:38.951
In the aquarium. That was you.

511
00:36:41.241 --> 00:36:42.663
He possessed you. too. didn't he?

512
00:36:43.827 --> 00:36:44.874
No.

513
