00:52:55.255 --> 00:52:58.475
<i>I've never woken up in the body</i>
<i>of someone I care so much about.</i>

771
00:52:59.968 --> 00:53:03.598
<i>It was the best and most terrifying day</i>
<i>of my life so far.</i>

772
00:53:05.599 --> 00:53:07.567
<i>You are the only reason why.</i>

773
00:53:09.561 --> 00:53:11.154
<i>Yours. A.</i>

774
00:53:41.301 --> 00:53:43.679
- Hey.
- Hey. babe. what are you doing here?

775
00:53:44.138 --> 00:53:45.685
I think we need to take a break.

776
00:53:47.599 --> 00:53:51.565
But this stuff between us is great.
our connection.

777
00:53:51.645 --> 00:53:53.067
It's really not.

778
00:53:54.398 --> 00:53:55.861
You don't see me.

779
00:53:55.941 --> 00:53:58.035
- I can see you.
- You have no idea who I am.

780
00:54:03.866 --> 00:54:05.084
Have a nice life.

781
00:54:21.216 --> 00:54:22.217
Hey.

782
00:54:24.928 --> 00:54:26.271
Are you kidding?

783
00:54:26.430 --> 00:54:29.730
I woke up feeling clearer
than I ever have in my entire life.

784
00:54:32.811 --> 00:54:34.525
Where are you today?

785
00:54:34.605 --> 00:54:36.232
<i>I wanna see you.</i>

786
00:54:48.076 --> 00:54:50.249
- What?
- Nothing.

787
00:54:54.124 --> 00:54:55.296
What?

788
00:54:55.918 --> 00:54:57.506
Your hand feels different.

789
00:54:57.586 --> 00:54:59.054
Yours feels the same.

790
00:55:02.424 --> 00:55:04.301
Thanks for not breaking up with Justin.

791
00:55:05.052 --> 00:55:08.022
Honestly. it was not easy.

792
00:55:22.194 --> 00:55:24.071
My uncle's in California right now.

793
00:55:24.154 --> 00:55:25.701
He barely uses this place. anyway.

794
00:55:26.949 --> 00:55:29.913
But I have to be home by
Sunday afternoon to hang with my mom.

795
00:55:29.993 --> 00:55:31.245
Oh. yeah. Right.

796
00:55:37.751 --> 00:55:39.719
So. this is our weekend?

797
00:55:40.921 --> 00:55:42.639
This is our weekend.

798
00:55:52.516 --> 00:55:54.564
Was that just because I look like this?

799
00:55:57.312 --> 00:55:58.734
It's because you're you.

800
00:56:01.400 --> 00:56:03.778
And 10% because you look like that.

801
00:56:05.654 --> 00:56:07.622
So. you actually remember everything?

802
00:56:09.324 --> 00:56:11.914
Well. it was like I went to bed Thursday
and woke up today.

803
00:56:11.994 --> 00:56:14.918
wearing a really strange bra.
thank you very much.

804
00:56:15.455 --> 00:56:18.300
But with all these memories. somehow.
with you in them.

805
00:56:19.877 --> 00:56:21.220
That must be really weird.

806
00:56:21.962 --> 00:56:23.760
No. it's amazing.

807
00:56:24.590 --> 00:56:27.139
A. I think you should let people
remember you.

808
00:56:27.718 --> 00:56:30.933
I think you should leave more memories
behind for more people

809
00:56:31.013 --> 00:56:32.560
and make more of a mark.

810
00:56:32.890 --> 00:56:35.979
You're such a bright.
beautiful. kind. funny...

811
00:56:36.059 --> 00:56:37.982
- Thing.
- Person.

812
00:56:38.896 --> 00:56:40.773
You're not freaked out anymore
that the first time that we met

813
00:56:40.856 --> 00:56:44.279
I let you kiss me. and
tell me all this personal stuff.

814
00:56:44.359 --> 00:56:46.828
without knowing that I was there?

815
00:56:47.779 --> 00:56:51.579
Well. you must kiss a lot of people.

816
00:56:54.119 --> 00:56:55.871
And hear a lot of personal stuff.

817
00:56:57.748 --> 00:56:58.966
Yeah. I...

818
00:57:02.169 --> 00:57:04.923
I've been a lot of boyfriends
and a lot of girlfriends.

819
00:57:06.048 --> 00:57:07.800
How does that not sound terrible to you?

820
00:57:08.300 --> 00:57:10.177
A. it sounds incredible.

821
00:57:11.553 --> 00:57:13.100
So why midnight?

822
00:57:13.263 --> 00:57:16.608
As far as I can tell.
I get 24 hours in each house.

823
00:57:17.225 --> 00:57:19.319
After that. I get pushed out.

824
00:57:20.103 --> 00:57:21.567
"Pushed out"?

825
00:57:21.647 --> 00:57:23.274
By the person whose place I'm taking.

826
00:57:23.523 --> 00:57:27.198
When they return. I don't know.
it's just what it feels like.

827
00:57:27.569 --> 00:57:29.196
What happens when you push back?

828
00:57:29.488 --> 00:57:32.492
I don't. When it's time to go.
it's not my body.

829
00:57:33.909 --> 00:57:37.413
Look. we just haven't gotten that far
in AP paranormal biology. yet.

830
00:57:37.704 --> 00:57:39.297
But I think it's being covered in the spring.

831
00:57:39.456 --> 00:57:40.708
Come on.

832
00:57:42.751 --> 00:57:45.880
So. do you consider yourself a boy or a girl?

833
00:57:48.590 --> 00:57:49.591
Yes.

834
00:57:57.891 --> 00:57:59.518
See you tomorrow.

835
00:57:59.601 --> 00:58:00.648
I promise.

836
00:59:28.565 --> 00:59:30.533
You wanna up and disappear. fine.

837
00:59:31.068 --> 00:59:34.663
You do it on a day when we're supposed
to go to D.C. together? Rude.

838
00:59:34.863 --> 00:59:36.201
I didn't forget. I just...

839
00:59:36.281 --> 00:59:40.457
You can't expect me to drop everything
that I'm doing for this family

840
00:59:40.577 --> 00:59:42.204
to drive for three hours

841
00:59:42.287 --> 00:59:45.377
to pick you up from a vacation you just
up and decided to give yourself.

842
00:59:45.457 --> 00:59:47.170
Apparently this family's not the only thing

843
00:59:47.250 --> 00:59:48.627
keeping you busy after work.

844
00:59:48.710 --> 00:59:50.007
Excuse me?

845
00:59:51.797 --> 00:59:55.017
Rhiannon. what the hell is going on with you?

846
00:59:58.762 --> 01:00:00.014
I just...

847
01:00:00.180 --> 01:00:01.602
You just what?

848
01:00:02.265 --> 01:00:03.266
I...

849
01:00:06.478 --> 01:00:08.151
Nothing. Nothing's wrong.

850
01:00:37.425 --> 01:00:40.015
Michael. I thought you were already up
and showered.

851
01:00:40.095 --> 01:00:42.849
Oh. my goodness.
We are gonna miss our flight.

852
01:00:43.807 --> 01:00:45.810
Hustle your ass. Michael.

853
01:01:05.579 --> 01:01:07.456
Hey. Can you pick me up today?

854
01:01:07.539 --> 01:01:08.710
Mikey. God damn it. Michael.

855
01:01:08.790 --> 01:01:10.667
My family's supposed to
fly to Honolulu today.

856
01:01:10.750 --> 01:01:13.879
If I go. tomorrow. I wake up as a kid
who's not flying back here.

857
01:01:15.505 --> 01:01:17.677
Silver Springs.
There's a Target down the highway.

858
01:01:17.757 --> 01:01:19.475
Meet me in the parking lot.

859
01:01:19.634 --> 01:01:21.728
Oh. my God. This kid does not exercise.

860
01:01:30.979 --> 01:01:32.652
- Michael.
- Shit.

861
01:01:33.356 --> 01:01:35.074
- Hey. Over here.
- Michael. Michael. get...

862
01:01:35.609 --> 01:01:36.610
Get back here.

863
01:01:36.693 --> 01:01:37.864
Okay. Slow down but don't stop.

864
01:01:37.944 --> 01:01:39.321
I can't hear you.

865
01:01:39.404 --> 01:01:40.742
- Shit. Do stop.
- What?

866
01:01:40.822 --> 01:01:43.200
- Stop. Stop.
- Shit. Shit.

867
01:01:43.283 --> 01:01:44.410
Michael!

868
01:01:45.827 --> 01:01:47.916
- Got it.
- Oh. God. Jolene's gonna kill me.

869
01:01:47.996 --> 01:01:49.292
Michael!

870
01:01:49.372 --> 01:01:51.294
- Get back here.
- Go. Go. Go.

871
01:01:51.374 --> 01:01:52.842
Okay. okay. okay.

872
01:01:54.044 --> 01:01:55.762
What are you doing with my son?

873
01:02:03.595 --> 01:02:04.642
I'm sorry.

874
01:02:04.763 --> 01:02:07.357
Well. had to be done.
Couldn't lose you to Hawaii.

875
01:02:08.391 --> 01:02:10.268
- But where were you?
- I couldn't come.

876
01:02:10.352 --> 01:02:13.106
Well. I was alone. and cold. and freaked out.

877
01:02:13.188 --> 01:02:15.402
And if my mom hadn't come.
I don't know what would've happened.

878
01:02:15.482 --> 01:02:19.863
Not to mention that she's pissed at me.
and I can't even begin to explain why.

879
01:02:19.945 --> 01:02:21.491
- I'm sorry.
- Where were you. A?

880
01:02:21.571 --> 01:02:23.285
- Getting a lung transplant.
- Shut up.

881
01:02:23.365 --> 01:02:25.203
I woke up in the evening.
I had no way to call you.

882
01:02:25.283 --> 01:02:27.411
I couldn't contact you.
They wouldn't even give me a phone.

883
01:02:27.494 --> 01:02:28.707
You're serious?

884
01:02:28.787 --> 01:02:29.879
Yes.

885
01:02:33.375 --> 01:02:35.213
Well. was it successful?

886
01:02:35.293 --> 01:02:36.465
I think so.

887
01:02:36.878 --> 01:02:38.255
Oh. God.

888
01:02:38.838 --> 01:02:40.715
I feel awful about abandoning you.

889
01:02:41.633 --> 01:02:45.809
No. No. it was my fault.
The weekend was my terrible idea.

890
01:02:47.430 --> 01:02:49.307
You think it was a terrible idea?

891
01:02:49.808 --> 01:02:51.651
What? No.

892
01:02:52.560 --> 01:02:54.688
I mean. it was amazing. too.

893
01:02:56.648 --> 01:02:59.367
I just... I think we need to be more careful.

894
01:03:01.611 --> 01:03:02.738
Yeah.

895
01:03:15.583 --> 01:03:17.836
<i>You know. I thought you'd "left" left.</i>

896
01:03:18.795 --> 01:03:20.138
<i>I'd never leave.</i>

897
01:03:21.548 --> 01:03:23.016
<i>Other than every day.</i>

898
01:03:33.101 --> 01:03:34.774
<i>Do you think we can keep doing this?</i>

899
01:03:36.313 --> 01:03:39.408
<i>I mean. not knowing who I'm gonna be</i>
<i>or where I'm gonna show up next?</i>

900
01:03:47.866 --> 01:03:50.790
<i>I guess I should probably go clean up</i>
<i>whatever chaos we caused for this kid.</i>

901
01:03:55.915 --> 01:03:57.542
<i>We'll figure this out.</i>

902
01:03:58.126 --> 01:03:59.218
<i>I promise.</i>

903
01:04:00.795 --> 01:04:02.047
Weird hands?

904
01:04:03.923 --> 01:04:05.425
Less than you'd think.

905
01:04:22.859 --> 01:04:24.827
Jo. I'm really sorry about the car.

906
01:04:26.863 --> 01:04:28.285
I feel horrible.

907
01:04:33.787 --> 01:04:35.414
Can I tell you what's happening?

908
01:04:39.751 --> 01:04:42.926
I'm in love with someone who wakes up
in a different body every day.

909
01:04:44.422 --> 01:04:47.267
Always the same age.
never the same person twice.

910
01:04:48.218 --> 01:04:51.097
Yesterday it was a kid
I needed to save from his family.

911
01:04:51.721 --> 01:04:53.439
Saturday. it was the guy in the pickup.

912
01:04:53.598 --> 01:04:55.937
And Sunday. it was someone
who couldn't make it to the cabin.

913
01:04:56.017 --> 01:04:58.896
So. that's what this is.

914
01:04:59.979 --> 01:05:03.695
Look. whatever weird. fake. role-playing.

915
01:05:03.775 --> 01:05:06.904
polyamorous-type shit you're into
nowadays. just don't involve me.

916
01:05:06.986 --> 01:05:09.330
- Jolene. it's real.
- And don't involve my goddamn car.

917
01:05:29.175 --> 01:05:32.600
Because I'm stupidly nice.
I'll excuse yesterday's absence.

918
01:05:36.558 --> 01:05:39.027
- Can't happen again. Rhiannon.
- It won't.

919
01:05:40.728 --> 01:05:42.856
Hey. where'd you go yesterday?

920
01:05:43.773 --> 01:05:45.821
I just didn't feel like being at school.

921
01:05:46.734 --> 01:05:48.987
Rhiannon. why are you not telling me
anything anymore?

922
01:05:49.070 --> 01:05:50.868
And who is that rando you hooked up with
over the weekend?

923
01:05:51.114 --> 01:05:53.082
What rando? What are you talking about?

924
01:05:54.117 --> 01:05:56.039
Jolene told her friends
that some guy abandoned you

925
01:05:56.119 --> 01:05:58.666
in the middle of the woods with no car.
That's. like. the ultimate rando move.

926
01:05:58.746 --> 01:06:00.419
Why is this everyone's business?

927
01:06:01.374 --> 01:06:04.173
It's not. But I figured it's mine
because I'm your friend.

928
01:06:05.503 --> 01:06:07.050
At least I used to be.

929
01:06:19.684 --> 01:06:21.277
- <i>Hello?</i>
- Is it you?

930
01:06:21.811 --> 01:06:22.812
<i>Yeah.</i>

931
01:06:23.855 --> 01:06:25.152
I got your message.

932
01:06:25.523 --> 01:06:26.524
Wow.

933
01:06:27.108 --> 01:06:29.782
<i>Yeah. I knew she had some dark thoughts.</i>

934
01:06:30.695 --> 01:06:32.492
<i>Maybe an hour ago I decided to draw</i>

935
01:06:32.572 --> 01:06:33.993
<i>something cheerful in one of her notebooks.</i>

936
01:06:34.073 --> 01:06:35.370
<i>Make her feel better.</i>

937
01:06:35.867 --> 01:06:37.744
<i>That's where she had it written down.</i>

938
01:06:43.541 --> 01:06:45.214
She's got it all planned out.

939
01:06:50.298 --> 01:06:53.802
If her dad finds her pills. she's gonna
drive into the side of an overpass.

940
01:06:58.014 --> 01:06:59.436
When does her dad come home?

941
01:06:59.807 --> 01:07:01.935
He doesn't leave the hospital until 5:00 a.m.

942
01:07:02.685 --> 01:07:04.028
He's in surgery until then.

943
01:07:07.607 --> 01:07:09.404
You've got to stop her.

944
01:07:09.484 --> 01:07:10.611
There's nothing I can do.

945
01:07:10.693 --> 01:07:11.865
You don't believe that.

946
01:07:13.238 --> 01:07:15.707
Call her father. Call a counselor.

947
01:07:16.491 --> 01:07:17.993
It's Kelsea's life. not mine.

948
01:07:18.076 --> 01:07:20.795
So. if she were gonna kill someone.
what would you do then?

949
01:07:21.079 --> 01:07:22.752
- I'd turn her in.
- Right.

950
01:07:23.206 --> 01:07:24.924
So how is this different?

951
01:07:25.083 --> 01:07:27.757
It's not fair of me to do something
that makes up her mind for her.

952
01:07:29.295 --> 01:07:31.009
So you never. ever get involved

953
01:07:31.089 --> 01:07:32.716
in the lives of the people you're inhabiting?

954
01:07:32.882 --> 01:07:33.883
I can't.

955
01:07:34.384 --> 01:07:36.637
What about Justin?
What made that so different?

956
01:07:37.929 --> 01:07:38.930
You.

957
01:07:42.308 --> 01:07:45.312
If you leave her at midnight.
she's going to go through with it.

958
01:07:46.062 --> 01:07:48.281
So. you're just gonna have to try and stay.

959
01:07:55.697 --> 01:07:57.495
I believe you can do it.

960
01:07:58.575 --> 01:08:00.623
And I need you to believe it. too.

961
01:08:02.412 --> 01:08:03.413
How?

962
01:08:07.292 --> 01:08:08.510
Push back.

963
01:08:12.297 --> 01:08:13.640
Stay with me?

964
01:08:41.784 --> 01:08:42.785
Honey?

965
01:08:43.328 --> 01:08:45.080
You need to get me help. Dad.

966
01:08:48.625 --> 01:08:50.878
I've been thinking about it for a long time.

967
01:09:16.944 --> 01:09:20.369
I'm up. Mom. Jeez.

968
01:09:23.618 --> 01:09:24.710
Sweetie?

969
01:09:31.042 --> 01:09:32.464
You feeling okay?

970
01:09:34.420 --> 01:09:37.595
Jo said you told her something kinda strange.

971
01:09:38.841 --> 01:09:41.390
About meeting someone
who's in a different body every day?

972
01:09:41.552 --> 01:09:42.804
It was a joke.

973
01:09:43.346 --> 01:09:44.438
All right.

974
01:09:46.724 --> 01:09:47.771
Hey.

975
01:09:50.144 --> 01:09:51.487
I love you. Rhi.

976
01:09:52.939 --> 01:09:55.283
If you ever need to talk. I'm always here.

977
01:10:01.280 --> 01:10:02.281
Dad?

978
01:10:05.326 --> 01:10:06.703
Do you still love Mom?

979
01:10:07.286 --> 01:10:08.879
Of course. I do. sweetheart.

980
01:10:11.332 --> 01:10:16.008
I don't think we can know what it's like
when you're in love with someone...

981
01:10:18.798 --> 01:10:20.175
And they change.

982
01:10:30.518 --> 01:10:31.645
Hey. what's up. slut?

983
01:10:31.728 --> 01:10:34.317
Hey. don't shame the slut.
Rhi. I'm proud of you.

984
01:10:34.397 --> 01:10:35.398
Stay slutty.

985
01:10:35.648 --> 01:10:37.400
Shut up. dumbass.

986
01:10:41.279 --> 01:10:42.952
- Hi.
- Hi.

987
01:10:44.699 --> 01:10:46.246
I really missed you yesterday.

988
01:10:47.702 --> 01:10:49.625
I'm sorry about those guys. It's my fault.

989
01:10:50.455 --> 01:10:53.254
It's nothing. So tell me everything.

990
01:10:58.629 --> 01:11:00.472
She's got more appointments tomorrow.

991
01:11:00.923 --> 01:11:05.725
Doctors. maybe an overnight stay.
Probably she goes on medication.

992
01:11:07.054 --> 01:11:10.479
I hope it turns out okay.
I mean. I think it could...

993
01:11:11.684 --> 01:11:13.061
But it's her life. so...

994
01:11:13.478 --> 01:11:16.857
It is. And you saved it.

995
01:11:18.149 --> 01:11:19.321
You stayed.

996
01:11:20.526 --> 01:11:21.869
I stayed.

997
01:11:22.987 --> 01:11:26.537
So that means you can
stay in someone else. maybe?

998
01:11:28.993 --> 01:11:30.586
Maybe I could.

999
01:11:31.287 --> 01:11:32.880
What are you doing tonight?

1000
01:11:34.916 --> 01:11:36.213
Date.

1001
01:11:36.667 --> 01:11:38.089
Not with you.

1002
01:11:39.045 --> 01:11:40.718
With her boyfriend. It's their anniversary.

1003
01:11:41.088 --> 01:11:42.681
I probably shouldn't miss it.

1004
01:11:43.716 --> 01:11:45.468
Well. maybe tomorrow then.

1005
01:11:53.309 --> 01:11:54.310
Can I kiss you?

1006
01:11:57.104 --> 01:11:58.105
Yeah.

1007
01:12:10.868 --> 01:12:11.869
Hi.

1008
01:12:14.080 --> 01:12:17.255
What are you doing up so late?
I thought you had a test tomorrow.

1009
01:12:19.126 --> 01:12:23.051
Mom. I know you and Dad
are trying to make it work.

1010
01:12:25.925 --> 01:12:31.476
But every day you can grow
a little bit closer to each other

1011
01:12:31.556 --> 01:12:35.186
or you can grow a little bit farther apart.

1012
01:12:37.103 --> 01:12:38.150
Okay.

1013
01:12:39.272 --> 01:12:40.273
Um...

1014
01:12:42.358 --> 01:12:45.237
Look. I know Dad is not who he was.

1015
01:12:46.612 --> 01:12:49.206
But you're not who you were. either.

1016
01:12:50.616 --> 01:12:52.584
Because we all change.

1017
01:12:55.830 --> 01:12:58.584
And you've changed. too.

1018
01:13:01.335 --> 01:13:02.507
So...

1019
01:13:03.796 --> 01:13:05.139
Please. just grow closer.

1020
01:14:22.416 --> 01:14:23.963
He's amazing. Rhiannon.

1021
01:14:24.835 --> 01:14:28.715
He's curious and kind. and handsome.

1022
01:14:30.466 --> 01:14:33.470
It's funny. I've known him for so long.
but I don't know much about him.

1023
01:14:34.053 --> 01:14:35.141
He's so shy at school.

1024
01:14:35.221 --> 01:14:37.474
Yeah. he's not the kinda kid
that's built for high school.

1025
01:14:38.683 --> 01:14:40.026
He's built for what comes next.

1026
01:14:41.352 --> 01:14:44.231
He remembers beautiful things beautifully.

1027
01:14:45.106 --> 01:14:46.608
He reads and he sees.

1028
01:14:46.691 --> 01:14:48.614
And he listens with every part of himself.

1029
01:14:49.902 --> 01:14:52.280
He sees what's funny in people
without ever being cruel.

1030
01:14:52.905 --> 01:14:56.330
Excuse me. I'll take this guy
if you don't want him. Who is he?

1031
01:14:56.659 --> 01:14:58.286
Oh. he's talking about himself.

1032
01:14:58.661 --> 01:14:59.662
Oh.

1033
01:15:00.454 --> 01:15:01.581
Hi.

1034
01:15:10.798 --> 01:15:12.550
So. do you have plans after school?

1035
01:15:12.675 --> 01:15:14.427
Um. it is after school.

1036
01:15:18.180 --> 01:15:19.648
What is happening?

1037
01:15:19.932 --> 01:15:21.354
Where are we going?

1038
01:16:24.371 --> 01:16:27.341
Do you think you could stay in Alexander
for one more day?

1039
01:16:30.711 --> 01:16:32.088
I'm not sure.

1040
01:16:34.006 --> 01:16:35.178
You did it with Kelsea.

1041
01:16:36.717 --> 01:16:39.015
With Kelsea it was easier. I think. 'cause...

1042
01:16:40.096 --> 01:16:41.848
I guess she didn't wanna be here anymore.

1043
01:16:44.058 --> 01:16:45.276
It's fine.

1044
01:16:46.227 --> 01:16:48.070
I get it. It's all good.

1045
01:16:53.734 --> 01:16:55.953
Would make things easier. though.
wouldn't it?

1046
01:17:00.866 --> 01:17:02.834
Rhi?

1047
01:17:04.245 --> 01:17:05.246
Hey.

1048
01:17:18.425 --> 01:17:21.679
Oh. my God. You stayed.

1049
01:17:23.222 --> 01:17:24.895
That's so exciting.

1050
01:17:34.108 --> 01:17:35.826
I knew exactly what it was.

1051
01:17:36.735 --> 01:17:37.987
Date night again tonight?

1052
01:17:38.487 --> 01:17:41.241
Tomorrow? I have to study for a test.

1053
01:17:42.199 --> 01:17:43.371
Tomorrow.

1054
01:17:44.493 --> 01:17:45.961
Okay.

1055
01:17:53.419 --> 01:17:56.673
Hi. Someone's excited for learning.

1056
01:18:37.171 --> 01:18:38.468
I love you.

1057
01:18:39.340 --> 01:18:40.512
I love you. too.

1058
01:18:43.510 --> 01:18:46.138
I better get home. or my mom will kill me.

1059
01:18:46.722 --> 01:18:48.440
Should we call it a night. then?

1060
01:18:50.726 --> 01:18:55.198
Actually. I guess I could come in
for. like. a minute.

1061
01:19:13.832 --> 01:19:16.130
- I think I should go now.
- Yeah.

1062
01:19:26.971 --> 01:19:30.225
Who forgets their own birthday?
Is that the new girl's fault?

1063
01:19:30.641 --> 01:19:32.143
Mom. I said I was sorry.

1064
01:19:32.726 --> 01:19:34.228
Past few days. I don't even recognize you.

1065
01:19:34.311 --> 01:19:36.525
I don't know if this is some
teenage angst bullshit.

1066
01:19:36.605 --> 01:19:37.651
but I won't have it.

1067
01:19:37.731 --> 01:19:39.984
- Mom. please don't be mad.
- I'm not mad.

1068
01:19:41.443 --> 01:19:43.908
Your aunts and I cooked literally
all day preparing that dinner.

1069
01:19:43.988 --> 01:19:46.116
which was at your request.
All of your favorites.

1070
01:19:46.615 --> 01:19:47.992
I'm just disappointed.

1071
01:19:48.701 --> 01:19:50.795
That was a shitty. selfish thing you did.

1072
01:19:54.456 --> 01:19:56.083
I'll make it up to them somehow.

1073
01:20:02.840 --> 01:20:04.558
You have a family that loves you.

1074
01:20:08.012 --> 01:20:09.855
Don't take that for granted.

1075
01:20:20.316 --> 01:20:22.489
- Hey.
- Hey.

1076
01:20:23.319 --> 01:20:25.117
Where have you been? You weren't in class.

1077
01:20:25.446 --> 01:20:27.449
- Rhiannon...
- Did you get in trouble?

1078
01:20:27.656 --> 01:20:29.203
Not as much as you might think.

1079
01:20:29.658 --> 01:20:32.161
- Rhiannon.
- Hey. are we still on for tonight?

1080
01:20:33.704 --> 01:20:37.002
His parents went out of town.
So. my place at 8:00?

1081
01:20:37.082 --> 01:20:38.709
Yeah. great. I'll see you then.

1082
01:20:38.792 --> 01:20:40.044
Hey. Rebecca.

1083
01:20:42.755 --> 01:20:44.223
TGI Friday.

1084
01:20:45.799 --> 01:20:47.346
I've been a bad friend.

1085
01:20:48.177 --> 01:20:50.680
I'm sorry. I'll tell you everything.

1086
01:20:50.763 --> 01:20:52.185
I don't need an explanation.

1087
01:20:53.599 --> 01:20:55.688
Well. good. because I'm not really sure

1088
01:20:55.768 --> 01:20:57.862
I would give you one
that would make any sense.

1089
01:20:59.355 --> 01:21:00.982
Are you and Alexander a thing now?

1090
01:21:01.732 --> 01:21:03.735
Uh. yeah.

1091
01:21:04.318 --> 01:21:05.786
I always thought you should be together.

1092
01:21:06.612 --> 01:21:07.909
You did?

1093
01:21:08.113 --> 01:21:09.114
Yeah.

1094
01:21:10.908 --> 01:21:12.410
I'm glad you're happy. Rhi.

1095
01:21:13.369 --> 01:21:15.372
I got practice. so. gotta go.

1096
01:21:42.731 --> 01:21:43.732
Wow.

1097
01:21:43.941 --> 01:21:45.659
What is this. the Last Supper?

1098
01:21:46.485 --> 01:21:48.078
More like a first date.

1099
01:21:48.570 --> 01:21:51.540
Turns out. he's a really great cook.

1100
01:21:52.282 --> 01:21:53.829
He's a really great guy.

1101
01:21:54.284 --> 01:21:55.877
Okay. I know.

1102
01:21:56.912 --> 01:21:58.164
So are you.

1103
01:21:58.247 --> 01:22:02.252
I mean. really great. I've never had
your cooking. so I can't speak to that.

1104
01:22:03.419 --> 01:22:08.300
Rhiannon. he's got a family
that loves him. and that he loves.

1105
01:22:09.591 --> 01:22:11.184
It's everything I've ever wanted.

1106
01:22:12.386 --> 01:22:14.889
Yeah. It's been nice.

1107
01:22:16.223 --> 01:22:17.566
But it's not mine.

1108
01:22:20.102 --> 01:22:23.151
I'm forcing Alexander
out of his own life. and it's wrong.

1109
01:22:24.565 --> 01:22:26.533
And the longer I stay.
the more I'm damaging him.

1110
01:22:27.359 --> 01:22:29.032
We'll go back to how it was.

1111
01:22:31.780 --> 01:22:33.828
Do you know Flynn in my algebra class?

1112
01:22:35.200 --> 01:22:37.164
You cannot. under any circumstance. be him.

1113
01:22:37.244 --> 01:22:39.918
If that's who you wake up in.
then don't even call me.

1114
01:22:43.667 --> 01:22:46.591
I mean. it can be Flynn.
It's not a deal-breaker.

1115
01:22:48.547 --> 01:22:50.345
I can't do it to anybody.

1116
01:22:54.303 --> 01:22:56.180
Not to Alexander. not to Flynn.

1117
01:22:58.640 --> 01:23:00.233
- Not to you.
- What are you saying?

1118
01:23:02.186 --> 01:23:04.483
I've been thinking about this over
and over and over.

1119
01:23:04.563 --> 01:23:06.026
I'm always going to be blocking you

1120
01:23:06.106 --> 01:23:07.653
from being with someone
who's perfect for you.

1121
01:23:14.573 --> 01:23:16.120
How could you say that?

1122
01:23:16.283 --> 01:23:18.786
Because Alexander's perfect for you.

1123
01:23:20.329 --> 01:23:22.457
- He's your type.
- You're my type.

1124
01:23:24.625 --> 01:23:26.798
Do you think I wanna live without you?

1125
01:23:28.587 --> 01:23:30.965
Do you think I'll ever be happy
in a place you're not?

1126
01:23:33.217 --> 01:23:35.264
Go back to a life that you're not in.

1127
01:23:35.344 --> 01:23:38.189
back to seeing only faces that aren't yours?

1128
01:23:38.388 --> 01:23:40.516
Hearing only voices that aren't yours?

1129
01:23:43.727 --> 01:23:45.320
You should be with him.

1130
01:23:48.440 --> 01:23:51.944
He's tall. slim. nice shoulders.

1131
01:23:58.075 --> 01:23:59.702
He's really smart.

1132
01:24:01.411 --> 01:24:05.252
He's incredibly kind. he's interesting.
and thoughtful on so many levels.

1133
01:24:05.332 --> 01:24:08.461
No. We can make it work. A.

1134
01:24:08.544 --> 01:24:09.921
I wanna believe that.

1135
01:24:11.296 --> 01:24:12.889
You know I wanna believe that.

1136
01:24:26.645 --> 01:24:29.148
Think about what happens
if you and I stay together.

1137
01:24:29.481 --> 01:24:31.358
I mean. really. truly. imagine it.

1138
01:24:34.069 --> 01:24:35.537
What does that look like in a year?

1139
01:24:37.489 --> 01:24:38.490
In 10 years?

1140
01:24:38.907 --> 01:24:40.375
What will happen to your life

1141
01:24:40.534 --> 01:24:43.333
if I'm the person in the world
that you're closest to?

1142
01:24:43.745 --> 01:24:45.247
How alone will it make you...

1143
01:24:46.665 --> 01:24:48.588
<i>If the one that you love is me?</i>

1144
01:24:49.668 --> 01:24:53.343
<i>And the one that you're with is me.</i>
<i>And you can't tell anyone about me.</i>

1145
01:24:54.381 --> 01:24:56.884
<i>How much is that gonna cut you off</i>
<i>from your family?</i>

1146
01:24:58.468 --> 01:25:01.347
<i>How much is that gonna cut you off</i>
<i>from everyone you know?</i>

1147
01:25:06.226 --> 01:25:09.401
<i>And what happens when I start waking up</i>
<i>as someone in a marriage?</i>

1148
01:25:11.565 --> 01:25:13.238
<i>Someone with kids?</i>

1149
01:25:16.153 --> 01:25:17.700
<i>What if we want a kid?</i>

1150
01:25:21.033 --> 01:25:24.456
<i>How will it feel for you to raise</i>
<i>that kid almost entirely alone</i>

1151
01:25:24.536 --> 01:25:27.460
<i>and not be able to explain to anyone</i>
<i>why that's what you chose?</i>

1152
01:25:30.792 --> 01:25:32.465
<i>Whose kid is that gonna be?</i>

1153
01:25:34.588 --> 01:25:35.885
<i>Is that gonna be my kid?</i>

1154
01:25:37.924 --> 01:25:40.973
Or will she be the kid of some guy
that you'll never see again

1155
01:25:41.053 --> 01:25:43.351
while my kid leaves you
the day after she's born?

1156
01:25:44.181 --> 01:25:45.899
Will my kid ever know her parents?

1157
01:25:46.475 --> 01:25:48.689
Or is she gonna have a life like mine
and always wonder...

1158
01:25:48.769 --> 01:25:49.941
Stop.

1159
01:26:01.031 --> 01:26:04.035
Most people know that their first love
won't be their only love.

1160
01:26:07.621 --> 01:26:09.248
But for me. you're both.

1161
01:26:18.590 --> 01:26:19.933
Say something.

1162
01:26:35.691 --> 01:26:38.035
We have three hours until midnight.

1163
01:26:40.696 --> 01:26:42.573
Let's not waste it.

1164
01:26:47.244 --> 01:26:48.832
What else?

1165
01:26:48.912 --> 01:26:52.667
In some minds. everything
feels muted and dim.

1166
01:26:52.749 --> 01:26:57.255
And in others. it's like everything
is supercharged and unfocused.

1167
01:26:57.963 --> 01:27:00.682
Like a radio flipping
from station to station.

1168
01:27:02.634 --> 01:27:04.102
Hard to get control of.

1169
01:27:06.054 --> 01:27:07.351
What else?

1170
01:27:08.974 --> 01:27:09.975
Um...

1171
01:27:11.560 --> 01:27:12.778
I'm thinking.

1172
01:27:19.776 --> 01:27:21.779
Am I going to see you again?

1173
01:27:29.161 --> 01:27:31.414
I have to believe that we will.

1174
01:27:33.832 --> 01:27:35.960
But you have to believe that we won't.

1175
01:27:41.089 --> 01:27:42.557
<i>Where are you going to go?</i>

1176
01:27:44.676 --> 01:27:45.848
<i>Far away.</i>

1177
01:27:47.387 --> 01:27:48.559
<i>New York.</i>

1178
01:27:50.015 --> 01:27:51.642
<i>Chicago. if I can get there.</i>

1179
01:27:53.894 --> 01:27:57.945
<i>Just some big. dense city</i>
<i>where there's lots of people to be.</i>

1180
01:28:02.027 --> 01:28:04.655
<i>There's still some things</i>
<i>I need to figure out about myself.</i>

1181
01:28:09.951 --> 01:28:13.751
Make marks. okay? Leave traces.

1182
01:28:16.041 --> 01:28:17.042
Yeah.

1183
01:28:23.048 --> 01:28:24.266
It's time.

1184
01:28:31.264 --> 01:28:32.982
Will you remember this tomorrow?

1185
01:28:35.435 --> 01:28:36.732
I'll remember everything.

1186
01:28:39.022 --> 01:28:40.399
So will I.

1187
01:28:46.196 --> 01:28:48.119
This is the nice note.

1188
01:28:52.202 --> 01:28:53.420
Good night.

1189
01:29:13.974 --> 01:29:15.192
Good night.

1190
01:29:31.741 --> 01:29:32.959
Katie.

1191
01:29:34.077 --> 01:29:35.704
Katie. you up?

1192
01:29:40.959 --> 01:29:42.006
Katie.

1193
01:30:38.266 --> 01:30:39.358
Hi.

1194
01:30:41.937 --> 01:30:44.782
Has anyone ever told you.
you have a nice smile?

1195
01:30:58.244 --> 01:30:59.666
Just being honest.

